Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.80,0:00:03.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is one of Kid's announcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.40,0:00:07.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and rack your brains,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.86,0:00:10.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,you modern-day Sherlock Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.23,0:01:57.01,Signs - Thief Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1000,0)}Kid, Conan, and the Ryoma Treasure Illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.32,0:01:57.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Kid the Phantom Thief announced that he'll \Nreturn Ryoma's treasures at 8:00 pm tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.01,0:02:00.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Already, over a hundred people are \Ngathered outside the Suzuki Museum,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.85,0:02:05.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,hoping to catch a glimpse of him!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.85,0:02:11.77,Signs,,0000,0060,15,,{\a7}Suzuki Museum
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.10,0:02:07.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! I wanna go there, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.10,0:02:11.77,Signs,,0150,0000,0000,,{\a9}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NKid                                                               Kid
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.55,0:02:09.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about it. It's dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.29,0:02:11.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I agree. Stay away from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.77,0:02:13.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.60,0:02:16.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For you to be worried about me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.54,0:02:19.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I never said I was worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.66,0:02:22.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, it's a chance to see the genuine \NKid the Phantom Thief in the flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.99,0:02:26.78,Signs,,0000,0060,15,,{\fad(0,800)}{\a7}Suzuki Museum
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.25,0:02:26.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Will Kid really show up tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.82,0:02:30.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is Kid, a phantom thief, \Ngoing to return stolen treasures?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.72,0:02:33.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And why is he going to do it tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.19,0:02:33.63,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)}Space reserved for Kid the Phantom Thief \Nto return treasures
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.63,0:02:35.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The mystery just keeps getting deeper.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.14,0:02:38.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It really is a mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.59,0:02:41.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he's going so far out of \Nhis way to return what he stole,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:43.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe it means he regrets the theft.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.98,0:02:47.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way that villain \Nfeels a shred of remorse!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.94,0:02:50.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna catch that bastard \Nfor sure this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.85,0:02:55.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And why does it have to be tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.28,0:02:57.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At first, he just said it would be "soon."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.61,0:02:59.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he suddenly announced \Nit'd be tomorrow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:02.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason, Aoko,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.06,0:03:04.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,is that it's going to rain tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.50,0:03:08.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He was waiting for the rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.66,0:03:12.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you really come up with \Nthat yourself, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.16,0:03:14.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.27,0:03:16.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what my instincts as a detective say!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.18,0:03:21.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So Kid was waiting for the rain \Nbefore setting the day and time?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.52,0:03:26.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! It looks like it could rain any minute now,\N and tomorrow's forecast calls for rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.38,0:03:29.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.14,0:03:31.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So why does it have to be a rainy day?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.85,0:03:36.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, maybe it has to do with the \N"washing" he mentioned in the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:41.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe because it's easier to blend in\N with with an umbrella and raincoat?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.39,0:03:42.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.74,0:03:45.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was just a gut feeling, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.28,0:03:47.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! That boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.47,0:03:51.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I mean, {\i1}boy,{\i0} a crimefighting \Npro like me knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.04,0:03:52.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.61,0:03:54.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So it did come from him...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.29,0:04:00.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know if Kid would base the date \Nand time of a crime on something so simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.68,0:04:03.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I pointed that out, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.57,0:04:05.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.78,0:04:09.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe Kid would do this \N{\i1}just{\i0} to return the treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.72,0:04:11.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.53,0:04:17.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tarumi, the exhibition sponsor, \Nand Hanamura, the appraiser, had an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.98,0:04:20.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They suspect Kid will make it look \Nlike he's returning the treasures,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.74,0:04:25.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,only to steal Ryoma's gun belt, \Nthe main attraction of the exhibition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.99,0:04:30.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's such a pain, you should just \Nhave them cancel the exhibition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.24,0:04:32.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.56,0:04:33.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.97,0:04:37.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That Tarumi guy is strongly \Nopposed to the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.98,0:04:39.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.09,0:04:42.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When it means Kid could steal the \Nmost important treasure of the bunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.73,0:04:44.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that weird behavior for a sponsor?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.88,0:04:47.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.08,0:04:51.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Especially since their exhibits have apparently\N been plundered by thieves several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.09,0:04:56.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So Tarumi and Hanamura are disciples
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.58,0:05:00.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,of that Gozu guy who tried \Nto kill me last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.83,0:05:05.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I hope you'll finally be able \Nto catch him this time, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.68,0:05:06.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Leave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.36,0:05:10.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a gas mask prepared just in case,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.12,0:05:13.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and we've decided on a code word \Nthat'll trip Kid up if he's in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.58,0:05:18.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We even installed metal detectors,\N since Kid will be carrying that pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.97,0:05:21.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be celebrating by this time tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.72,0:05:25.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the precious \Ninfo as always, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.27,0:05:30.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But I still wonder what he meant \Nby "washing" in his notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.93,0:05:34.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably just a play on Ryoma's words.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.22,0:05:35.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.31,0:05:40.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think Kid the Phantom Thief \Nis that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.14,0:05:47.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think a pro thief would go to all \Nthe trouble just to return stuff, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.54,0:05:50.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My guess is that \Nhe's got some other purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.81,0:05:53.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Another purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.42,0:05:58.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Rain... washing... \NMaybe they're hinting at something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:06:02.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although I'm not Kid, so what do I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.93,0:06:09.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One at a time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.37,0:06:11.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please step through the gates one at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.29,0:06:12.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next person, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.76,0:06:13.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't push!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.58,0:06:14.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.10,0:06:14.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.81,0:06:15.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that Kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.80,0:06:16.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.76,0:06:17.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.96,0:06:19.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.73,0:06:21.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.28,0:06:25.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the problem?! I should be able \Nto wear what I want!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.09,0:06:26.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Creep...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.76,0:06:29.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't look anything like the real deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.05,0:06:33.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place, Kid would never \Njust stroll through the gates.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.48,0:06:37.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be too sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:40.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But anyway, I'm not that fat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.75,0:06:42.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Kid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.86,0:06:46.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.51,0:06:49.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let the game begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.35,0:07:05.32,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Space reserved for Kid the Phantom Thief \Nto return treasures
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.54,0:07:05.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. They sure were polite \Nto reserve me a space.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.32,0:07:08.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Like the moniker goes, \NKid is a "phantom" magician.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.32,0:07:12.28,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Space reserved for Kid the Phantom Thief \Nto return treasures
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.82,0:07:10.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not gonna follow your guidelines...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.58,0:07:12.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he'll show up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.33,0:07:29.55,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Space reserved for Kid the Phantom \NThief to return treasures
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.90,0:07:18.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, son?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.32,0:07:21.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.56,0:07:26.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A phantom thief wouldn't appear \Nwhere they tell him to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.39,0:07:29.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you're right about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.55,0:07:33.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn cosplayer. \NThinks this is a convention...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.44,0:07:36.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, there's something that bothers me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.62,0:07:37.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.58,0:07:43.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't picture Kid, a thief, just coming \Nto return treasures that he stole.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.76,0:07:48.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I suspect he has some ulterior motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.91,0:07:50.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,An ulterior motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.20,0:07:53.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Rain... washing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.61,0:07:57.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe those are major clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.11,0:08:00.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you really come up with \Nthat by yourself, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:03.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:10.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Little bastard... \NDon't tell me he's on to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.46,0:08:20.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Phantom Lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.84,0:08:36.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The length is 17 centimeters,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.48,0:08:38.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so that's about...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.70,0:08:40.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,About this size?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.74,0:08:45.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,June 24th, 1867.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.15,0:08:49.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryoma mentioned this pistol in a \Nletter to his older sister, Otome.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.85,0:08:53.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"It's 17 centimeters and holds five bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.29,0:09:00.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's smaller than a dagger, but can \Nkill a man from 90 meters away."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:01.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.90,0:09:04.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.52,0:09:10.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How'd you smuggle that in? \NDid you go through the gates?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.02,0:09:14.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. All I had to do was remove the lead \Nfrom the grip and waltz right through.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.22,0:09:15.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really light this way, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.86,0:09:20.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although lugging this many of them \Nwas a pain in the neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.23,0:09:26.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you one thing. This time, I really \Ndid come just to return the stolen goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:28.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So don't get in my way, Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.85,0:09:29.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See ya!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.72,0:09:32.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait! Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:42.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't push.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.64,0:09:44.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Walk slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.06,0:09:45.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.88,0:09:53.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.28,0:09:55.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Ran-nee-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.80,0:09:57.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.13,0:10:00.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you could get crushed \Nin this crowd, Conan-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.45,0:10:03.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Imagine what it'll be like \Nby the time Kid announced.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.74,0:10:06.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? There's something on your right arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.94,0:10:07.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.56,0:10:10.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.31,0:10:13.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Iron One"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.13,0:10:16.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that some kind of secret code?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.15,0:10:21.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, did you bump into something \Nin the exhibit room?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.35,0:10:24.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I was pushed against the \Ncase of the gun belt exhibit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.46,0:10:30.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, come on. Give me a \Nlittle more time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.08,0:10:37.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I wonder how \NKid the Phantom Thief will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.46,0:10:39.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's something to look forward to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.72,0:10:42.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He isn't our enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.05,0:10:43.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a colleague.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:46.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Since he's an accomplice...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.12,0:10:48.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You two look really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.56,0:10:53.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though Kid may be coming to \Nsteal your precious treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.04,0:10:57.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about, young man?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.26,0:10:58.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not happy at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.98,0:11:03.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. And besides, he's not \Ncoming to steal treasures tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.10,0:11:04.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's coming to return them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.91,0:11:06.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if that's really it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.93,0:11:10.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What else would he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.37,0:11:15.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If he stole something, the police would \Nbe on him like that and it'd be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.87,0:11:18.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe Kid won't be the one \Nwho's arrested this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.34,0:11:22.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Take good care of that ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.07,0:11:27.29,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Handicraft Corner
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.65,0:11:27.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that brat?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.58,0:11:29.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Little turd...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.85,0:11:32.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like he's figured it out, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.98,0:11:34.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.54,0:11:37.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give your filthy natures
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.25,0:11:40.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,a good washing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.69,0:11:43.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How's the entrance?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.97,0:11:48.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir! Nobody's turned around and left \Nwhen they saw the metal detectors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.26,0:11:51.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there any problems \Nat the metal detectors?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.02,0:11:54.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. And no one's come through \Ncarrying that pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.73,0:11:56.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on in the \NRyoma exhibition room?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.58,0:12:00.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At the moment, no one who \Nlooks like Kid is around,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.46,0:12:02.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I wonder if he's even \Ngoing to show up at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.98,0:12:04.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dumbass!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.38,0:12:08.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid has never announced an \Nappearance and then blown it off!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.77,0:12:14.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Five more minutes until \Nthe time he announced...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.10,0:12:20.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When the show starts, I'm counting on you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.72,0:12:21.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Jii-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.42,0:12:26.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just too bad that I won't \Nget to see the wonderful show.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.98,0:12:30.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, ladies and gentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.45,0:12:33.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's showtime!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.56,0:12:38.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Kid did have \Nanother motive, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.57,0:12:39.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.87,0:12:42.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you'll find out soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.20,0:12:44.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.26,0:12:47.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid may show up any time now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.17,0:12:49.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just an elementary school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.31,0:12:51.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave Kid to you police.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.12,0:12:54.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I don't wanna get wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.40,0:12:59.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Get wet? What is he talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.32,0:13:02.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, there are too many people in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.88,0:13:06.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Security isn't worth a damn\N when it's like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.26,0:13:08.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.82,0:13:09.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut it out! Don't touch me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.98,0:13:11.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my! I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.56,0:13:14.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You look like my deceased husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.86,0:13:18.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.32,0:13:32.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kid the Phantom Thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.75,0:13:35.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid-sama, you're so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.76,0:13:37.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's standing on the gun belt case!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.71,0:13:39.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What were you talking about, "washing"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.95,0:13:44.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll catch you and wash you to the bone!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.38,0:13:47.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the idea. But to wash \Nsomething, you need water.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.70,0:13:51.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Observe as I make it rain in this one room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.64,0:13:53.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,R-Rain?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.96,0:14:10.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a... He used fire \Nto activate the sprinklers!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.78,0:14:12.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And now I shall take my leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.86,0:14:16.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait! I thought you were \Ngonna return those three items!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.10,0:14:21.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This shower will make everything clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.38,0:14:24.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as rain washes away muddy water.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.05,0:14:29.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Can't see him with the steam...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.89,0:14:33.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That villain! He must have tampered \Nwith the sprinkler's water pressure!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.99,0:14:41.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.78,0:14:44.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.40,0:14:46.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The exit is this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.78,0:14:51.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's very crowded, so please \Nproceed slowly towards the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.32,0:14:55.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Footprints!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.77,0:14:58.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Follow wet footprints \Nthat go through the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.57,0:15:02.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But there are wet footprints \Nall over the floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.04,0:15:04.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.25,0:15:05.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.93,0:15:09.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he waited for a rainy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.86,0:15:12.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's not the only reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.43,0:15:15.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what about the three items \Nhe said he was gonna return?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.64,0:15:18.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He left them on top of the gun belt case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.39,0:15:22.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is no good. My blood got on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.64,0:15:27.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it seems that all three were just \Nreplicas, so there's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.54,0:15:30.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is this gun belt...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:32.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.21,0:15:35.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The security system inside \Nthe case has been destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.58,0:15:40.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then the gun belt inside is a fake that \NKid switched out with the real one?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.21,0:15:41.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.72,0:15:43.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He got us!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.00,0:15:50.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The explanatory plaque on that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.45,0:15:51.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's dripping from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.40,0:15:55.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Paint...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.28,0:15:58.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.39,0:16:02.85,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2000,0)}This gun belt was a fake all along. \NThey made a large quantity of them on \Nthe assumption that they would be stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.78,0:16:02.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He stuck a duplicate plaque with the same \Nmessage in watercolor paint over the original,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.85,0:16:07.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so when water hit it, the paint would run, \Nrevealing the secret message underneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.86,0:16:11.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, Inspector. After \Nthe washing comes the drying.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:15.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So put these two clowns out \Nto dry! I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.57,0:16:19.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! My sleeve was wet \Nfrom the rain outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.46,0:16:23.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So the watercolor letters on the gun belt \Nexplanation plaque came off reversed on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.54,0:16:26.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So? What's this secret message underneath?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.11,0:16:27.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.62,0:16:31.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"This gun belt was a fake all along..."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.47,0:16:37.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They made a large quantity of them on the \Nassumption that they would be stolen. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.93,0:16:43.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The important part was that the thefts \Nmade news and got a lot of attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.58,0:16:43.77,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)}Ryoma Relics Stolen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.09,0:16:48.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So they mass-produced replicas \Nof the items beforehand
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.20,0:16:52.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and used third parties to sell them\N to wealthy Ryoma fans,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.43,0:16:55.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,who were all told they were getting the item\N that was stolen the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.98,0:17:00.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The beauty of this scheme is that even if \Nthe buyers realize later they bought a fake,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.90,0:17:02.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,they can't report it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.66,0:17:08.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If they filed a complaint, they'd have to \Nadmit they secretly bought stolen merchandise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.00,0:17:15.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Phantom Lady's crime didn't come \Nto light after those three items were stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.28,0:17:20.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then she entrusted you with all \Nthe replicas she'd collected
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.17,0:17:24.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and asked you to expose \Nthose two con men, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.59,0:17:29.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The crime would need both an exhibition \Nsponsor who knew they were fakes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.28,0:17:34.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and a crooked appraiser who would claim \Nthose replicas were the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.90,0:17:37.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.61,0:17:40.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryoma poseur phantom thief!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.27,0:17:46.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Is the message on this plaque true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.13,0:17:48.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No! It's bull!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.08,0:17:52.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place, where is this \Nso-called "large quantity" of fakes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.90,0:17:56.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All I see are this light \Npistol made out of plastic,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.37,0:17:58.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,a counterfeit sake cup,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.25,0:17:59.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and a phony letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.94,0:18:00.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.81,0:18:05.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I just noticed I'm wearing \Nthis gun belt with the pistol!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.07,0:18:07.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,M-Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.09,0:18:11.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A card on the belt says, "Borrowed \Nfrom Tarumi-shi's warehouse"!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:16.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Blast you, Kid! He used the crowd \Nto slap belts around all our waists!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.90,0:18:18.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.46,0:18:22.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You sabotaged the security system yourself \Nto make it look like the belt was stolen
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.90,0:18:26.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and then afterwards sold copies of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.08,0:18:28.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.27,0:18:29.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.37,0:18:33.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This exhibit also has a plaque with a \Nmessage under the washed-away paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.00,0:18:33.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.72,0:18:36.16,Signs - readability,,0000,0000,0000,,The materials used are new and the method of \Nproduction is modern, so in conclusion, this\N hanging scroll can't be from the Bakumatsu period.\N- Kid the Phantom Thief
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.42,0:18:36.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Pull," it says...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.52,0:18:39.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He wants me to pull on this scroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.14,0:18:46.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.35,0:18:48.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryoma's letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.24,0:18:50.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And they're all multiple \Ncopies of the same one!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.77,0:18:56.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They look exactly the same as the \None left on the gun belt case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.65,0:18:58.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's a setup!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.03,0:19:00.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid set us up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.57,0:19:06.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! There's no proof that \Nwe made and sold these forgeries!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.50,0:19:09.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.09,0:19:11.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just did what Kid's plaque said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.71,0:19:14.17,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,The materials used are new and the method of \Nproduction is modern, so in conclusion, this\N vase can't be from the Bakumatsu period.\N- Kid the Phantom Thief
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.14,0:19:13.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Crush."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.40,0:19:19.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. There's a ton of sake cups inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.92,0:19:23.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like each one \Nof them has blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.66,0:19:29.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we run a DNA test on the blood, it will \Nbecome obvious who fabricated these cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.95,0:19:33.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you lie like before and say you \Ntouched them all with a wounded finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.69,0:19:37.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You wiped your own blood \Non all of these cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.20,0:19:42.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sure we'll find plenty of evidence\N when we search your warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.00,0:19:46.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Probably a mountain of unsold fakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.12,0:19:49.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you figured out I was Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.30,0:19:51.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I look like a middle-aged guy\N you'd see anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.46,0:19:52.58,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.04,0:19:58.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even fake plastic pistols take up a lot \Nof space if you carry them together.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.70,0:20:02.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And even more so if you've also got \Na bunch of letters and sake cups.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.51,0:20:04.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So I looked for somebody in the crowd
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.94,0:20:09.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,who had an especially slim lower half \Ncompared to the rest of their body.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.41,0:20:14.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I found you, pretending to be fat so \Nyou could hide all those replicas.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.67,0:20:18.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And of course, you're in disguise, \Nso there's no sweat to be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.46,0:20:24.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So I stuck this button-sized transmitter \Nsticker to your skinny ankle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.09,0:20:30.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I located your position with my tracking \Nglasses and called out to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.34,0:20:36.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So? Are you gonna turn me over\N to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.64,0:20:37.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.92,0:20:40.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This time I'll let you go, \Nout of deference to Ryoma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.04,0:20:44.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a Ryoma fan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.05,0:20:46.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My mom is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.08,0:20:50.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,She once played Ryoma's big sister, Otome, \Nand fell madly in love with Ryoma.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.01,0:20:57.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But the reviews called her too cute to play \NOtome, which turned out to be a career boost.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.20,0:21:02.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it sounds like we're \Nboth no match for our moms.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.64,0:21:06.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.40,0:21:08.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Both?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.29,0:21:11.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.80,0:21:13.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Phantom Lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.37,0:21:17.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Aoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.44,0:21:21.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to me getting the runs, I was holed up \Nin the museum bathroom the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.89,0:21:25.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And you stayed with me, so you didn't get \Nto see Kid the Phantom Thief, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.44,0:21:31.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay. Anyway, he's probably just some \Nmiddle-aged fat guy who looks like a thug.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.60,0:21:35.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not that fat!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.03,0:21:42.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can say that now, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.97,0:21:50.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, until we meet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.96,0:21:55.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to follow the adventures of \Nthat pint-sized great detective, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.56,0:21:58.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See you next illusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.61,0:23:35.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That means it's almost Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.47,0:23:38.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I intended to spend a quiet \NChristmas Eve at home,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.56,0:23:41.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but Aoko's gonna have a party and \Nwants me to help her with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.56,0:23:44.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And what's this? Kid has sent out \Nanother advance notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.41,0:23:46.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It sure as hell wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.66,0:23:48.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna take a break that night!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.82,0:23:51.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on {\i1}Magic Kaito 1412{\i0}:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.82,0:23:53.16,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy Night: Two Kid the Phantom Thieves
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.21,0:23:53.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Holy Night: Two Kid the Phantom Thieves!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.39,0:23:56.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Step right this way! Watch carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.62,0:23:58.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the illusion!
